formula: f(Q, n) = Sum_{d|n} d*f(Q-1, d); here Q=5.
Dirichlet g.f. zeta(s)*zeta(s-1)*zeta(s-2)*zeta(s-3)*zeta(s-4). Dirichlet convolution of A038991 with A000583. - _R. J. Mathar_, Mar 31 2011
mathematica: a[n_] := DivisorSum[n, #*DivisorSum[#, #*DivisorSum[#, #*DivisorSum[#, # &] &] &] &]; Array[a, 50] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Dec 02 2015, after _Joerg Arndt_ *)
f[p_, e_] := Product[(p^(e + k) - 1)/(p^k - 1), {k, 1, 4}]; a[1] = 1; a[n_] := Times @@ (f @@@ FactorInteger[n]); Array[a, 100] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Aug 29 2019 *)
